# Overview

This project is a basic test of LED PWM control.

# Description

The LED PWM duty cycle change function is a triangle wave, with period
of 4 seconds.

PWM duty cycle resolution is 8 bits.

# Support

`20150704a_timer-calculator` support tool is used. Parameter values are:

Parameter       Value
--------------- --------------
clock           4
interval        15.625
timer width     8
init delay      2

Interval is calculated like this: 2 (seconds, half period), divided by
256 (steps, PWM resolution).

The following resulting values are used:

Result          Value
--------------- --------------
prescaler       32
TMR0 init val.  14

# Hardware Setup

GP2 pin is used as PWM output. Other pins are unused (input).

